		[641] heading 'What Is Administrate?'
		[643] paragraph ''
			StaticText "Administrate is a library for Rails apps that automatically generates admin dashboards. Administrate's admin dashboards give non-technical users clean interfaces that allow them to create, edit, search, and delete records for any model in the application."
		[644] paragraph ''
			StaticText 'Administrate solves the same problem as'
			[645] link 'Rails Admin', url='https://github.com/sferik/rails_admin'
			StaticText 'and'
			[646] link 'ActiveAdmin', url='http://activeadmin.info/'
			StaticText ', but aims to provide a better user experience for site admins, and to be easier for developers to customize.'
		[647] paragraph ''
			StaticText 'To accomplish these goals, Administrate follows a few guiding principles:'
		[648] list ''
			[649] listitem ''
				ListMarker '•'
				StaticText 'No DSLs (domain-specific languages)'
			[650] listitem ''
				ListMarker '•'
				StaticText 'Support the simplest use cases, and let the user override defaults with standard tools such as plain Rails controllers and views.'
			[651] listitem ''
				ListMarker '•'
				StaticText 'Break up the library into core components and plugins, so each component stays small and easy to maintain.'
